# ============================================================================
# ClawBench environment variables
# ============================================================================
# Copy this file to `.env` (gitignored) and fill in the values below.
# For a step-by-step walkthrough, see docs/installation.md.

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# PurelyMail  --  disposable email for each test run (required)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# ClawBench provisions a fresh email address per run and deletes it afterward.
#
#   1. Sign up at https://purelymail.com/
#   2. Add and verify a domain you own in the PurelyMail dashboard
#   3. Generate an API key under Account -> API Access
#   4. Paste the key and domain below
#
# Format notes:
#   PURELY_MAIL_API_KEY  -  typically 40+ alphanumeric characters
#   PURELY_MAIL_DOMAIN   -  bare domain, no scheme (e.g. clawbench.example.com)
PURELY_MAIL_API_KEY="api_key_here"
PURELY_MAIL_DOMAIN="your_domain_here"

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# HuggingFace  --  optional auto-upload of run outputs
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# When both are set, each run's output directory is uploaded to the configured
# dataset repo and the local copy is replaced with an `uploaded.json` marker.
# Pass `--no-upload` to a single run to skip even when credentials are set.
#
#   Token: create at https://huggingface.co/settings/tokens  (needs write scope)
#   Repo:  must already exist; create at https://huggingface.co/new-dataset
# HF_TOKEN="hf_..."
# HF_REPO_ID="your-org/your-dataset-name"

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Container engine override (optional)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# ClawBench auto-detects `docker` or `podman`. Set this to force one.
# CONTAINER_ENGINE="podman"
